				\begin{document}$$EF = f_{{{\text{forest}}}} A_{{{\text{forest}}}} \left( {\frac{{E_{RM} + E_{B} + E_{S} }}{n} + E_{{{\text{OTEC}}}} + E_{{{\text{Microalgae}}}} + E_{{{\text{Tuna}}}} } \right)$$\end{document}where ERM, EB, and ES are the CO2 emissions associated with raw material production, building, and installation and scrapping, respectively, while EOTEC, EMicroalgae, and ETuna stand for the CO2 emissions associated with the operation of OTEC, microalgae cultivation, and tuna aquaculture, respectively. In addition, fforest = 1.26 gha/ha represents the equivalence factor of the forest.

